Just the Moves

Make your move
You're out of positions, nice job!

What is this? And why?

I was inspired by the book Move First, Think Later to try and create a chess training tool for myself that focuses on tightening the feedback loop between seeing a position, choosing a move, and feedback. This website will show you random positions from World Championship matches, let you make your best move, then tell you how bad your move was compared to the best move. Also, I had a LOT of fun making something this ugly and hacked together.
